<p>But the problem doesnâ€™t stop there. In the realm of soft skills, the â€œcode monkeyâ€ mentality can be even more damaging. If youâ€™re not making an effort to improve your communication skills, learn how to mentor others, or collaborate effectively with non-developers, youâ€™re not just limiting your own growthâ€”youâ€™re also missing out on the opportunity to learn from others. Working with legal, marketing, or design teams can be incredibly rewarding and educational. At Mailchimp, for example, we work closely with our product and design teams to ensure that weâ€™re delivering the best possible experience for our users, and Iâ€™ve learned a ton from those interactions.</p>

